                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14475409" author="musketyr" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:08:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;any chance to get this fixed soon (in next release)? it&apos;s pretty annoying to force users to use custom builds instead of official ones.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475317" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 06:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied a privileged block around it. It should work now&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475495" author="musketyr" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 07:02:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wouldn&apos;t be so sure. Privileged block wasn&apos;t helping for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6405&quot; title=&quot;AccessControlException with Google App Engine and indy version of the Groovy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6405&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6405&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - see the b.patch which didn&apos;t help&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475433" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 07:27:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggest you try &lt;a href=&quot;http://ci.groovy-lang.org:8111/repository/download/Groovy_Jdk7Build/369:id/target/distributions/groovy-sdk-2.1.10-SNAPSHOT.zip?guest=1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ci.groovy-lang.org:8111/repository/download/Groovy_Jdk7Build/369:id/target/distributions/groovy-sdk-2.1.10-SNAPSHOT.zip?guest=1&lt;/a&gt; to see if it works or not&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475354" author="musketyr" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 09:04:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok, I&apos;ve tried &lt;a href=&quot;http://ci.groovy-lang.org/repository/download/Groovy_Jdk7Build/372:id/target/distributions/groovy-binary-2.2.2-SNAPSHOT.zip&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ci.groovy-lang.org/repository/download/Groovy_Jdk7Build/372:id/target/distributions/groovy-binary-2.2.2-SNAPSHOT.zip&lt;/a&gt; and it looks working well&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475467" author="musketyr" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 02:04:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;actually the 2.2.2 release versions still contains the bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475653" author="kdabir" created="Sat, 22 Mar 2014 03:11:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fails for me with GAE 1.9.0 ,Groovy 2.2.2, Java 1.8, OS X Mavericks &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475638" author="blackdrag" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 06:37:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;and the stack trace is exactly the same?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475654" author="musketyr" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 07:18:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;stacktrace2.txt is the latest stacktrace. looks pretty similart to me, just the package name changed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475672" author="musketyr" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 02:08:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;just verified it still exists in 2.3.0-beta-1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475629" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 02:44:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;since the control block did not work I am now doing the forceful method and just swallow the exception&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475689" author="marceloverdijk" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 04:36:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also affects Groovy 2.2.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
